The paper focuses on optimizing communication in parallel BFS on distributed memory systems, which involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and graph algorithms/data structures (cs.DS). The proposed techniques involve compression and sieving of messages, which are related to network protocols and algorithms (cs.NI) and performance analysis and optimization (cs.PF). The experiments are conducted on a large-scale cluster, which involves system-level design and analysis (cs.SY).
